## Functions

### AnalyzeArguments() {#ad996415c84f27a48afd2fd7dc653efea}

<MemberDefinition
  template={<>template &lt;typename ArgT&gt;</>}
  prototype={<>static void AnalyzeArguments (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/ccstate">CCState</a> &amp; State, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallvectorimpl">SmallVectorImpl</a>&lt; <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/ccvalassign">CCValAssign</a> &gt; &amp; ArgLocs, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallvectorimpl">SmallVectorImpl</a>&lt; ArgT &gt; &amp; Args)</>}
  labels = {["static"]}>
Analyze incoming and outgoing function arguments.

We need custom C++ code to handle special constraints in the ABI like reversing the order of the pieces of splitted arguments. In addition, all pieces of a certain argument have to be passed either using registers or the stack but never mixing both.

Definition at line <a href="#l00454">454</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/msp430/msp430isellowering-cpp">MSP430ISelLowering.cpp</a>.
</MemberDefinition>
